description: Reinforcement of computational thinking and problem-solving skills. Application of object-oriented programming principles including class design, encapsulation, inheritance, polymorphism,
interfaces, abstract classes, aggregation and association. Additional topics include version control, use of debuggers and exception handling. This is the second course for students interested in
pursuing a computer science major or related
